Wrap the UPDATE statement in a DO $$ ... $$ block with DECLARE, and add GET DIAGNOSTICS + RAISE NOTICE after line 12:

```sql
DO $$
DECLARE v_deduped int;
BEGIN
  WITH dupes AS (
    SELECT id, row_number() OVER (
      PARTITION BY lower(coalesce(match_description,'')), match_direction, match_min_amount, match_max_amount,
                   match_transaction_type, coalesce(set_vendor_name,''), set_vendor_id, coalesce(set_expense_category,''),
                   auto_status, kind
      ORDER BY priority ASC, created_at ASC
    ) AS rn
    FROM public.receipt_rules WHERE is_active
  )
  UPDATE public.receipt_rules r
  SET is_active = false, deactivated_at = now()
  FROM dupes WHERE r.id = dupes.id AND dupes.rn > 1;

  GET DIAGNOSTICS v_deduped = ROW_COUNT;
  RAISE NOTICE 'Deduplicated receipt rules: deactivated %', v_deduped;
END $$;
```

This fix is safe because: (1) it uses the same pattern as migration 20260714000011, (2) GET DIAGNOSTICS only reads the row count without modifying state, (3) RAISE NOTICE is purely informational, (4) the core UPDATE logic is unchanged, and (5) the DO block ensures atomic execution.

Use the same escaping pattern already established in the codebase (bulk-messages.ts:28):

```typescript
// At line 339, replace:
const needles = criteria.match_description.split(',').map((n) => n.trim()).filter(Boolean)

// With:
const needles = criteria.match_description.split(',').map((n) => {
  const trimmed = n.trim()
  // Escape SQL ILIKE wildcards: %, _, and \ (escape character itself)
  return trimmed.replace(/[%_\\]/g, '\\$&')
}).filter(Boolean)
```

This approach:
1. Escapes percent signs (%) to literal % characters
2. Escapes underscores (_) to literal _ characters  
3. Escapes backslashes (\) to literal \ characters (PostgreSQL requires this)
4. Aligns with the existing pattern used in bulk-messages.ts
5. Allows needles to be matched literally, not as wildcard patterns
6. Is safe for PostgREST/PostgreSQL ilike patterns

